esp_peer.c is an independent UDP peer derived solely from esp.c
(construct_esp_packet and esp_mainloop), esp-seqno.c (verify_packet_seqno),
openssl-esp.c (encrypt_esp_packet and decrypt_esp_packet), and gpst.c
(gpst_esp_send_probes and gpst_esp_catch_probe) in OpenConnect commit
2035601b64a5360a46d18e08937e7f654b3230f2. It preserves the ESP-in-UDP
framing, AES-CBC and truncated-HMAC suites, sequence-zero behavior,
OpenSSL explicit-IV chain, and GlobalProtect ICMP echo exchange while using
an independently generated explicit IV for each server packet.

